            <h2>FAQs</h2>
            <h3>What is the cheapest day to book flights? </h3>
            <p>Tuesday is often considered the cheapest day to book flights due to lower demand and frequent airline sales. </p>
            <h3>How can I find exclusive airline deals and offers? </h3>
            <p>Subscribe to airline newsletters and set fare alerts on platforms like Faresmatch to stay updated on sales and discounts. </p>
            <h3>Why is it important to compare airfare between airlines? </h3>
            <p>Comparing airfares allows you to identify the most affordable option for your route, helping you save money. </p>
            <h3>Which airlines offer the best deals for domestic US travel? </h3>
            <p>Delta, United, and American Airlines are popular choices, but budget carriers like Southwest and Spirit Airlines also offer competitive prices. </p>
            <h3>How far in advance should I book flights for the lowest fares? </h3>
            <p>Booking your flight at least 1–3 months in advance for domestic travel or 2–6 months for international travel often yields the best prices. </p>
            <h3>Can promo codes help in booking cheap flights? </h3>
            <p>Yes, using promo codes or discount coupons during booking can significantly reduce airfare costs. </p>
            <h3>How can flexibility with travel dates help save money? </h3>
            <p>Flexible dates allow you to take advantage of off-peak travel times, which are usually cheaper. </p>
            <h3>What role do budget airlines play in finding cheap flights? </h3>
            <p>Budget airlines, such as Southwest and Frontier, often provide lower fares for travelers willing to forgo some amenities. </p>
            <h3>Are last-minute flight bookings ever cheap? </h3>
            <p>Last-minute bookings are rarely cheap. Planning and booking early is the best way to secure affordable tickets. </p>
            <h3>How can I avoid hidden fees when booking flights? </h3>
            <p>Carefully read the airline's policies and check for additional charges like baggage fees or seat selection costs to avoid unexpected expenses. </p>

